1. Parse model name using `parseNormalizePullModelRef()` (handles cloud/local source suffixes)
2. Call `getExistingName()` to resolve case-insensitive filesystem names
3. Load manifest via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(n)`
4. Call `m.Remove()` which:
   - Deletes the manifest file itself
   - Prunes empty directories recursively
5. Call `m.RemoveLayers()` which:
   - Scans all remaining manifests to build a set of in-use digests
   - Deletes blob files only if no other manifest references them
   - Safely handles missing files

