### 4. MODEL NAME PARSING & VALIDATION

**Main Parsing Function:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775466849324-bqmnv0/types/model/name.go`

**Name Format (BNF):**
```
name ::= [host "/"] [namespace "/"] model [":" tag] ["@" digest]
host   = pattern: alphanum|"_" followed by alphanum|"-"|"_"|"."|":"  (length 1-350)
namespace = pattern: alphanum|"_" followed by alphanum|"-"|"_"       (length 1-80)
model = pattern: alphanum|"_" followed by alphanum|"-"|"_"|"."       (length 1-80)
tag   = pattern: alphanum|"_" followed by alphanum|"-"|"_"|"."       (length 1-80)
digest = sha256 format with ":" or "-"
```

**Defaults Applied:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775466849324-bqmnv0/types/model/name.go` (lines 38-59)

```go
const (
	defaultHost           = "registry.ollama.ai"
	defaultNamespace      = "library"
	defaultTag            = "latest"
	defaultProtocolScheme = "https"
)

func DefaultName() Name {
	return Name{
		Host:           defaultHost,
		Namespace:      defaultNamespace,
		Tag:            defaultTag,
		ProtocolScheme: defaultProtocolScheme,
	}
}
```

**Parsing Process:**
1. `ParseName(s)` → parses string and applies defaults
2. `ParseNameBare(s)` → parses string without defaults
3. Parsing uses `cutPromised()` to handle required separators
4. Last ":" before "/" is treated as tag separator
5. "/" separators denote host/namespace/model boundaries
6. "://" indicates protocol scheme

**Validation:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775466849324-bqmnv0/types/model/name.go` (lines 268-281)

```go
func (n Name) IsFullyQualified() bool {
	parts := []string{
		n.Host,
		n.Namespace,
		n.Model,
		n.Tag,
	}
	for i, part := range parts {
		if !isValidPart(partKind(i), part) {
			return false
		}
	}
	return true
}
```

**Filepath Construction:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775466849324-bqmnv0/types/model/name.go` (lines 292-302)

